-- Bubka, Bach, Oswald Are Among Six Candidates for IOC Presidency
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-06-07T07:55:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-07/bubka-bach-oswald-are-among-six-candidates-for-ioc-presidency.html
Six candidates will compete in
September’s election to replace  Jacques Rogge  as president of
the  International Olympic Committee .  Thomas Bach, Sergey Bubka, Richard Carrion, Ser Miang Ng,
Denis Oswald and Ching-Kuo Wu officially announced their
candidacies by the deadline of midnight June 6, the IOC said
today in a statement.  The candidates will present their programs to the full IOC
membership during the Olympic organization’s July 3-4
extraordinary session in Lausanne, Switzerland. The election
will be held Sept. 10 in Buenos Aires.  Rogge will step down in September after 12 years as head of
the Olympic body.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  